                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/msus-402" class="program-course-title">
              MSUS 402 Systems Thinking and Sustainability (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-30856" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Management (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/612">Desautels Faculty of Management</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      MSUS              : Examines interconnected dynamics of organizations and social, economic, and ecological systems. Introduces systems thinking principles to foster learning, inform organizational decision-making, and solve real-world problems. Covers problem diagnosis and resolution of organizational and societal sustainability issues through causal loop diagrams, stock-and-flow mapping, group model building, computational simulations and case studies.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Jeroen Struben (Winter)                  </p>

    
