                <div id="node-35023" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Religious Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Religious Studies              : Social justice and human rights issues as key aspects of modem religious ethics. Topics include: the relationship of religion to the modem human rights movement;
religious perspectives on the universality of human rights; the scope and limits of religious freedom; conflicts between religion and rights.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Daniel M Cere (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
