    <p>Offered by: Civil Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Civil Engineering              : State-of-the-art water resources management techniques; case studies of their application to Canadian situations; identification of major issues and problem areas; interprovincial and international river basins; implications of development alternatives; institutional arrangements for planning and development of water resources; and, legal and economic aspects.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Van-Thanh-Van Nguyen (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-0-6)</li>
              <li>Prerequisite (Undergraduate): CIVE 323 or equivalent</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

